A windowless room awaits Louis van Gaal on Sunday. Whatever the result at Huish Park, Manchester United's manager will take a right in the tunnel and enter Yeovil Town’s self-proclaimed ‘Bunker’.

It’s the ominous-sounding office of Gary Johnson and where the manager has been plotting the downfall of English football’s biggest name for the last six days.

Van Gaal will slip inside to share a bottle of red post-match, but has been warned he may have to bring his own.

