‘If Louis watched us against Leyton Orient he’d probably feel they could put out their Under 14s against us.

‘We’ve had to get those games out of the way first if you like. This is a different kettle of fish. Hopefully the boys will go in with a different feeling, without the pressure of the points. Now it’s finally here we just can’t wait.’

Johnson - who says his experience managing Latvia stands him in good stead for games such as this - cannot be far off legend status in this pocket of the West Country. He was the man who won promotion to the Football League in 2003 and then did the unthinkable by taking Yeovil to the Championship two years ago.

‘If we win they might even put a statute up of me,’ he laughed. ‘I reckon I’ve earned one already, but the chairman says I’ve got to do a little bit more yet. I’m only 5’7” so it wouldn’t take a lot of metal, would it?’

Johnson’s side are going to have to show more than a bit of mettle if they want to inflict anything worse than a cheap bottle of wine on Van Gaal. 

 

 

